cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with fine-grained visual classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves optimizing class means, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of bounding box estimation also suggests a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) subfields.
